  "prompt": "What is the best app to learn English?",
  "response": "There are several great apps for learning English, and the best one for you may depend on your learning style and goals. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **Duolingo**: Offers a gamified learning experience with lessons that cover vocabulary and grammar in a fun, interactive way.\n\n2. **Babbel**: Focuses on conversational skills and real-life dialogues, making it ideal for practical language use.\n\n3. **Rosetta Stone**: Known for its immersive approach, Rosetta Stone emphasizes learning through context and visual aids.\n\n4. **Busuu**: Offers interactive lessons with a social feature where you can practice with native speakers.\n\n5. **Memrise**: Uses spaced repetition and mnemonic techniques to help with vocabulary retention.\n\n6. **HelloTalk**: Connects you with native speakers, allowing for language exchange and real-life conversation practice.\n\n7. **FluentU**: Utilizes real-world videos, such as movie clips and inspirational talks, to teach language in context.\n\nWhen choosing an app, consider what aspect of English you want to focus on\u2014such as speaking, listening, grammar, or vocabulary\u2014and try out a few to see which ones match your preferences.",
